  "prompt": "What universities does GAIN Capital recruit new grads from? What majors are they looking for?",
  "response": "GAIN Capital, a financial services firm known for its online trading platforms, tends to recruit new graduates from a variety of universities, particularly those with strong finance, business, economics, and technical programs. While the specific institutions they target can vary, they often look favorably on universities known for their finance or quantitative programs, such as:\n\n- Ivy League schools (e.g., Harvard, Princeton)\n- Top state universities (e.g., University of Michigan, University of California)\n- Specialized financial or technical schools\n\nAs for majors, GAIN Capital looks for candidates from disciplines including, but not limited to:\n\n- Finance\n- Economics\n- Business Administration\n- Mathematics\n- Statistics\n- Computer Science\n- Data Science\n\nAdditionally, they may consider candidates with strong analytical skills and relevant experience in quantitative analysis or trading. Always check their career page or recruitment announcements for the most current information.",
